"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-07-parisolympics-olympic-gold-medals-worth-us950\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France - The gold medal at the Paris Olympics is reportedly worth US$950 (approximately J$148,000).\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9797212882120813, \"rank\": 0.01469211082446158, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to an article by Forbes Australia, the medal is possibly the highest in value in the history of the games, primarily because of the record-high prices for gold.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 135, \"end\": 141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"score\": 0.9999999408495359, \"rank\": 5.598036753647709e-08, \"text\": \"Forbes\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\"}, {\"begin\": 142, \"end\": 151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9891364177254638, \"rank\": 0.006258668309264783, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It surpasses the US$708 (approximately JM$110,000) record for the 2012 London Olympics.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Forbes Australia says the Olympic gold medal weighs 529 grams, with more than 95.4 per cent of the medal actually made of silver (505 grams).\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"score\": 0.9999999408495359, \"rank\": 5.598036753647709e-08, \"text\": \"Forbes\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\"}, {\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9891364177254638, \"rank\": 0.006258668309264783, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Six grams consist of pure gold, which serves as the plating for the medal, and 18 grams consist of iron.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Iron is not usually a metal used in the making of Olympic medals, but it's not just ordinary iron.\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes from the Eiffel Tower, the universally recognised symbol of Paris and France.\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999761507732029, \"rank\": 2.3849795558987372e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 793, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9797212882120813, \"rank\": 0.01469211082446158, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the gold medal were made of pure gold, it would be valued at approximately US$41,161-more than JM$6 million.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time pure gold medals were presented was in 1912.\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The silver medal weighs 525 grams, with 507 grams made of silver and 18 grams of iron.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its value, based on the July 24 spot price for silver and iron, is approximately US$486 (approximately JM$76,000).\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medal weighs 455 grams and consists of 415.15 grams of copper, 21.85 grams of zinc, and 18 grams of iron.\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its podium value is approximately US$13 (approximately JM$2,000).\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": []}]}"